## Today youâ€™re going to learn how to use and create: **functions**

Creating a function lets you make your own blocks! There are two parts to a function: 

* Making a newly named block that has all of the code you want to run inside of it.  
 <xml>
 <block type="procedures_defnoreturn" editable="false">
    <mutation/>
    <title name="NAME">get only nectar</title>
    <statement name="STACK">
      <block type="bee_ifFlower">
        <title name="LOC">atFlower</title>
        <statement name="DO">
          <block type="maze_nectar" deletable="false"/>
        </statement>
      </block>
    </statement>
  </block>
  </xml>

* The single green block itself that you use, or call, to run the function you created.  
<xml>  
<block type="when_run" deletable="false" movable="false"/>
  <block type="procedures_callnoreturn" id="callMe">
    <mutation name="get only nectar"/>
  </block>
  </xml>

Prepare to get familiar with functions, learn how to edit them, and create your own!
MARKDOWN
